From: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
Date: Tue, 14 Apr 2026 07:05:40 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] ==== data activity monitor ====

mm/damon: introduce data attributes monitoring

DAMON monitors only data access activities.  This limits usage of DAMON.
Using DAMOS_STAT and filters, users can get more detailed page level
information.  It is still constrained to DAMOS filter types and induce
high overhead.

Extend DAMON to monitor not only data access but general and multiple
data attributes.  Allow users to register multiple data attributes of
their interest.  Add per-attribute counter to each region, and increment
the counter every sampling intervals if the sampling memory of the
region is matched to the attribute.

Each data attribute is defined as a chain of filters.  The filters are
similar to DAMOS filters.  The type supports anonymous page type.

Hence, with this patch series, users can know how much of each DAMON
region is filled with anonymous or file-backed pages with low overhead.

In future, the filter type will be extended for all DAMOS filter types.
After that, it will even support access events, and eventually replace
the access monitoring.

Signed-off-by: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
